{"id": "codex-20260515-095945-0e1efrxxxxxx", "agent": "codex", "description": "You are doing Round 1 implementation from the architecture revamp contract at .agents/plans/ARCH-REVAMP-IMPL-CONTRACT.md. Read section 2.2 for your slice assignments and section 1 for the non-negotiable standards.\n\nImplement slices C-1, C-2, C-3, and C-4 in sequence. For each slice: make the code change, run python -m py_compile on the modified file, confirm it passes.\n\nC-1 (P0 \u2014 do this first): In ai-stack/mcp-servers/hybrid-coordinator/core/llm_client.py at lines 460-473, add the header \"X-AI-Profile\": \"coordinator-internal\" to the outbound POST to the switchboard. This breaks the circular hints loop (coordinator calls switchboard, switchboard calls coordinator for hints). Only inject this header when no profile header is already set on the outbound request.\n\nC-2 (P1): In ai-stack/local-agents/agent_executor.py, find _probe_remote_fallback() and fix it: HTTP 401, 403, and 404 responses must be treated as UNHEALTHY (return False), not healthy. Currently they are silently treated as healthy.\n\nC-3 (P1): In ai-stack/local-agents/agent_executor.py, replace all hardcoded 127.0.0.1:8080 and 127.0.0.1:8003 endpoint strings with env var reads (LLAMA_CPP_URL and COORDINATOR_URL respectively). Use os.environ.get() with the existing pattern in the file.\n\nC-4 (P2): In ai-stack/local-orchestrator/router.py, fix the QUERY_PATTERNS list (around line 97-108). The pattern r\"^can (you|i|we)\" incorrectly routes implementation requests like \"can you implement X\" as QUERY. Fix: either remove this pattern entirely, or narrow it to only match pure questions (e.g. require the next word to be a question indicator, not an action verb).\n\nStandards to follow (from contract \u00a71):\n- Never hardcode ports \u2014 use env vars\n- httpx only (no requests)  \n- python -m py_compile must pass on every changed file\n- No vendor model names\n\nAfter completing all four slices, run: python -m py_compile ai-stack/mcp-servers/hybrid-coordinator/core/llm_client.py ai-stack/local-agents/agent_executor.py ai-stack/local-orchestrator/router.py\n\nReport: for each slice, show the exact diff you made and confirm py_compile passed.", "output_file": ".agents/delegation/outputs/codex-20260515-095945-0e1efrxxxxxx.log", "pid": 898811, "status": "running", "created": "2026-05-15T16:59:45Z"}
{"id": "codex-20260515-103706-savtkpxxxxxx", "agent": "codex", "description": "You are doing Round 3 from the architecture revamp contract at .agents/plans/ARCH-REVAMP-IMPL-CONTRACT.md. Read section 2.2 (slices C-5 and C-6) and section 1 (non-negotiable standards).\n\nImplement C-5 and C-6 in sequence.\n\nC-5 (P2): In ai-stack/local-orchestrator/router.py, create a thin compatibility adapter that emits canonical RoutingDecision from ai-stack/mcp-servers/hybrid-coordinator/routing_contract.py. The live callers are orchestrator.py:21,78,117 and __init__.py:10. Requirements:\n- Import RoutingDecision and RoutingTier from routing_contract.py\n- The existing AgentBackend enum must remain importable (backward-compat shim)\n- New routing decisions returned to callers should be RoutingDecision dataclasses\n- No vendor model names in routing code\n- Use RoutingTier.LOCAL, RoutingTier.REMOTE_PAID etc instead of bare strings\n\nC-6 (P2): Staged retirement of ai-stack/local-agents/task_router.py:\n- Update callers (self_improvement.py:27, __init__.py:10 or wherever they import task_router) to use routing_contract.RoutingDecision instead\n- Keep task_router.py file in place but add a deprecation comment at the top: '# DEPRECATED: use ai-stack/mcp-servers/hybrid-coordinator/routing_contract.py'\n- Do NOT delete the file yet (staged retirement \u2014 deletion is Round 4 after G-3 approval)\n\nStandards from contract section 1:\n- Never hardcode ports/URLs\n- httpx only (no requests)  \n- python -m py_compile must pass on every changed file\n- No vendor model names \u2014 use RoutingTier enum values\n\nAfter each slice: run python -m py_compile on modified files.\nFinal: run python -m py_compile on all changed files together.\n\nReport the exact diff for each slice and confirm py_compile passed.", "output_file": ".agents/delegation/outputs/codex-20260515-103706-savtkpxxxxxx.log", "pid": 1055856, "status": "done", "created": "2026-05-15T17:37:06Z"}
