{"id": "gemini-20260518-121439-w2gzy1", "agent": "gemini", "role": "implement", "description": "You are a research synthesizer for the NixOS-Dev-Quick-Deploy AI harness. Your role is to research domain capability gaps and produce structured findings that the orchestrator (Claude) will use to author capability domain PRDs.\n\nPROJECT CONTEXT:\n- NixOS-first, flake-based AI harness on a ThinkPad P14s (AMD Renoir APU, 27GB RAM, no dGPU)\n- Primary tools: Qwen3.6-35B local LLM, hybrid-coordinator (port 8003), AIDB (port 8002)\n- Routing profiles: local-tool-calling, default, remote-reasoning (see docs/architecture/routing-profile-inventory.md)\n- AIDB namespaces are partitioned per domain; MemoryBroker writes via POST /api/memory/facts\n- All tooling MUST be provisioned via nixpkgs or Nix flake inputs - no bare pip install\n\nTASK: Research and produce structured findings for THREE capability domains that will be activated in this harness. For each domain, produce:\n\n1. Top 5 recommended Nix packages (from nixpkgs) that should go in a domain dev shell\n2. The most important AIDB knowledge namespace content to seed (5-10 bullet points of what to index)\n3. Key safety/dual-use concerns specific to this domain\n4. 3-5 concrete acceptance criteria for when the domain reaches 'validated' state\n5. Recommended routing profile split (which query types \u2192 which profile: local-tool-calling vs remote-reasoning vs default)\n\nThe three domains to research:\n\nDOMAIN A: mobile-web\n- Context: Web backend/dashboard capability exists; need mobile app toolchains, frontend workflows, accessibility/security testing\n- Existing: Playwright (likely in nixpkgs), modern web stack, OWASP web checks\n- Gaps per master PRD: Android SDK / Flutter shell support, iOS builds impossible (no macOS/Xcode), web/mobile dev shells, accessibility audits (WCAG), MASVS mobile security checklists, component libraries\n\nDOMAIN B: scientific-research\n- Context: Python/R scientific stacks available in nixpkgs; Jupyter support via nixpkgs\n- Existing: numpy/scipy/matplotlib ecosystem, LaTeX tooling in nixpkgs\n- Gaps per master PRD: reproducibility defaults (seeds, versions, uncertainty, provenance), literature-search/citation pipelines, notebook-to-report pipeline, scientific project templates, simulation/HPC support\n\nDOMAIN C: gis-systems\n- Context: Essentially absent from harness today\n- Existing: PostGIS can be enabled via nixpkgs; GDAL available in nixpkgs\n- Gaps per master PRD: GDAL/OGR/PROJ/GeoPandas/Rasterio/Shapely/QGIS stack, CRS discipline rules, Natural Earth/OSM/elevation data ingestion, tile generation, raster/vector processing workflows, GIS AIDB namespace\n\nFor each domain, also identify: what is the single most important first follow-on slice after the domain reaches 'proposed' state?\n\nFormat your response as structured markdown with clear headers for each domain. Be specific about Nix package names (search your knowledge for the correct nixpkgs attribute names). Focus on what is realistic for a local-first NixOS system, not cloud-dependent tools.", "output_file": ".agents/delegation/outputs/gemini-20260518-121439-w2gzy1.log", "pid": null, "status": "done", "tokens_in": null, "tokens_out": null, "created": "2026-05-18T19:14:39Z"}
{"id": "gemini-20260518-124604-0mziqk", "agent": "gemini", "role": "implement", "description": "Research task for the NixOS-Dev-Quick-Deploy harness. You are the research synthesizer.\n\nPROJECT CONTEXT:\n- NixOS 25.11 flake-based system (nixpkgs stable 25.11)\n- flake.nix already has devShells.default (statix, deadnix, alejandra) and devShells.bitnet-benchmark\n- Need to add 5 new domain dev shells: security, embedded, mobile-web, scientific, gis\n- All packages MUST be from nixpkgs 25.11 stable \u2014 verify they exist there\n\nTASK: For each dev shell below, produce the EXACT Nix mkShell definition including:\n1. packages list with verified nixpkgs 25.11 attribute paths\n2. shellHook with domain-specific env vars and a clear 'echo' summary\n3. Note any packages that may NOT be in nixpkgs 25.11 stable (use unstable overlay alternative if so)\n\nIMPORTANT: Cross-check each package against nixpkgs 25.11. If uncertain, provide the correct attribute path AND note the uncertainty.\n\n--- SHELL 1: security ---\nRequired: semgrep, bandit (Python), trivy, shellcheck, cppcheck\nNote: semgrep may require python3Packages.semgrep; bandit = python3Packages.bandit; trivy = pkgs.trivy\n\n--- SHELL 2: embedded ---\nRequired: verilator, ghdl-llvm (or ghdl), yosys, openocd, gcc-arm-embedded (or pkgsCross.arm-embedded.stdenv.cc), qemu\nNote: ARM cross-toolchain in nixpkgs is pkgsCross.armv7l-hf-multiplatform or similar. RISC-V is pkgsCross.riscv64. Check exact attribute paths.\n\n--- SHELL 3: mobile-web ---\nRequired: flutter, android-tools, nodejs_22, nodePackages.lighthouse (or playwright), chromium\nNote: flutter in nixpkgs 25.11 may be flutter or flutter340 or similar. Check exact attribute. playwright = playwright-driver or pkgs.playwright-test\n\n--- SHELL 4: scientific ---\nRequired: python3 with (numpy, scipy, matplotlib, pandas, jupyter, snakemake), pandoc, texlive minimal, R (optional)\nNote: jupyter = python3Packages.jupyter or python3Packages.jupyterlab. snakemake = python3Packages.snakemake or pkgs.snakemake\n\n--- SHELL 5: gis ---\nRequired: gdal, geopandas (python3Packages), qgis, spatialite-tools, proj\nNote: geopandas = python3Packages.geopandas; spatialite may be libspatialite or spatialite-tools; qgis may be large \u2014 note if headless-only alternative exists\n\nFor each shell also provide a one-line shellHook echo summarizing available tools.\n\nFormat: valid Nix expression fragments that can be dropped directly into flake.nix devShells.", "output_file": ".agents/delegation/outputs/gemini-20260518-124604-0mziqk.log", "pid": null, "status": "done", "tokens_in": null, "tokens_out": null, "created": "2026-05-18T19:46:04Z"}
